                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.115 St 21/469: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-12-20T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1926—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. For Hill. H–110. Your H–200, December 17, 1926, and Department’s 330 of
                    December 18, 6 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d121fn23">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Department advised that Standard Oil made payment of $400,000 December 20 to
                    National City Bank account Reparation Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
